answer_options.answer_text: Internal vertical walls divide the accumulator container into sections. A maximum of 10kg (22 lbs.) is allowed in any section of the accumulator container.

Internal vertical walls separating cells and/or segments must be constructed of steel 0.9mm (0.035 inch) thick or aluminum 2.3mm (0.090 inch) thick. Internal vertical walls must be a minimum of 85 percent of the height of the attached perimeter vertical wall.
The floor or bottom of the accumulator must be constructed of steel 1.25mm (0.049 inch) thick or aluminum 3.5mm (0.125 inch) thick.
The perimeter vertical walls forward, aft, left, and right must be constructed of steel 0.9mm (0.035 inch) thick or aluminum 2.3mm (0.09 inch) thick.

answer_options.answer_text: The battery container material must be fire resistant according to UL90-V0, FAR20 or equivalent.
Regenerating energy is allowed and unrestricted but only when the vehicle speed is ≥ 5kph. It is not allowed at vehicle speeds < 5kph.
mplausibility is defined as a deviation of more than 5% pedal travel between the sensors.
Each accumulator container must have a prominent indicator, such as an LED that will illuminate whenever a voltage greater than 60V DC is present at the vehicle side of the AIRs.
